Adjust rack to top position, then preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Trim, then halve @Brussels Sprouts{16%ounce}. Mince or grate
@Garlic{2%cloves} (save the rest for later). Zest, then halve @Lemon{1}. Dice
@Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch pieces (no need to peel). Place in a
large #pot with salted water to cover. Boil until tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

Drain potatoes. Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} in same pot over low heat. Add
@Garlic{2%cloves}(minced); cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Return
potatoes to pot; mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Stir in
@Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Keep covered until
ready to serve.

Meanwhile, toss Brussels sprouts in a large #bowl with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{} and a pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Place Brussels sprouts and
1 lemon half on a #baking sheet{}. (Use the rest of the lemon as you like.)
Roast on top rack until golden brown, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Pat @Sirloin Steak{28%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}; season generously with
@Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{} in a large #pan
over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per
side. Turn off heat; remove steak from pan and let rest. Wipe out pan.

Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} in same #pan over medium heat. Add remaining
@Garlic{2%cloves} and @Rosemary{1%sprig} (we sent more) and cook, stirring often,
until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Reduce heat to low. Add @Beef Demi-Glace{2},
@Dijon Mustard{4%teaspoon}, and @Water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until thoroughly
combined, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in any resting juices from steak. Turn off heat.
Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}(to taste). Remove and discard garlic and
rosemary.

Slice rested steak against the grain. Squeeze as much juice from roasted lemon
as you like over Brussels sprouts. Sprinkle with lemon zest and @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon}(to taste). Divide steak, Brussels sprouts and mashed potatoes
between plates. Spoon sauce over steak and serve.